    bracket_map = {}
    stack = []
    for i, char in enumerate(code):
        if char == '[':
            stack.append(i)
        elif char == ']':

                bracket_map[start] = i
                bracket_map[i] = start

            memory[pointer] = (memory[pointer] + 1) % 256
        elif command == '-':
            memory[pointer] = (memory[pointer] - 1) % 256
        elif command == '.':
            output += chr(memory[pointer])
        elif command == '[':

                code_pointer = bracket_map[code_pointer]
        elif command == ']':
            if memory[pointer] != 0:
                code_pointer = bracket_map[code_pointer]
        
        code_pointer += 1
    
    return output
